com.ibm.mqlight.api

Interface Delivery

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    BytesDelivery, MalformedDelivery, StringDelivery

    public interface Delivery
    This interface is used to represent the delivery of a messages to the MQ Light client. It is sub-classed to represent the delivery of specific types of message data (e.g. binary and textual data).

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  Delivery.Type
      Possible types of data that can be associated with this delivery.

    • Method Detail

      • getType

        Delivery.Type getType()
        Returns:
        the type of the delivery. This is provided to simplify casting this interface to the more specific BytesDelivery and StringDelivery types.

      • confirm

        void confirm()
             throws StateException
        Confirms receipt of this delivery.
        Throws:
        StateException - if confirmation is not applicable or required. This is the case if any of the following conditions are true:
        • the quality of service is QOS.AT_MOST_ONCE.
        • auto confirmation of delivery is enabled.
        • delivery has already been confirmed.
        • the network state is such that delivery cannot be confirmed.

      • getQOS

        QOS getQOS()
        Returns:
        the quality of service used to receive the messaging being delivered.

      • getShare

        String getShare()
        Returns:
        the share name associated with the destination from which the message was received. A value of null is returned if the destination was not subscribed to with a share value.

      • getTopic

        String getTopic()
        Returns:
        the topic to which the message, being delivered, was originally published.

      • getTopicPattern

        String getTopicPattern()
        Returns:
        the topic pattern that was used to subscribe to the destination from which this message was delivered.

      • getTtl

        long getTtl()
        Returns:
        the remaining time-to-live time, for the message being delivered, in milliseconds.

      • getProperties

        Map<String,Object> getProperties()
        Returns:
        a Map of properties associated with the message being delivered. Keys will be non-null and values will be one of the following types: null, Boolean, Byte, Short, Integer, Long, Float, Double, byte[], and String.
